  "difficultyLevel": 8,
  "lyrics": "808 caught the jam DJ Flair, make the money flare Everywhere I go, I keep a pocket full of dough Everywhere I go, I keep a wallet full of dough Nah, fuck that, let's be honest Every single month, I be waitin' on my food stamps And if I wasn't rappin', I'd be homeless, thinkin', damn I am not a grown man, even though I'm grown, man Keep a foil in my hand, block as hot as oil in the pan Poppin' bowls till they boil and they burn, boys, take it Boy, I stay sellin' work, so I smoke for free I mean, hopefully, I make my re-up Big bro in blue dreads, bangin' C's up Amoebra I've been spittin' myself so many ways that I feel like Amoeba Stretchin' myself way too thin, and these drugs don't help Bein' a thug don't help, I created my own hell, I refuse to ask for help Since 1993, I've been tryin' to set my mind free Mind died down by these high beams As life strikes me like lightning, I keep fightin' The only feasible outcome, outgunned and eye-strung I run into the same nightmares that I've had since I was young So I run, run, run, run away real fast Take a blast of the glass, knock me back on my ass So I run, run, run, run away real fast Take a blast of the glass, knock me back on my ass There's no more rebels in the fridge Business getting thin when the pixie burstin' in And now the business is extinct and I ain't seen it straight in weeks Exist among the weak, but tell myself there's nothing wrong with fighting Exist among the weak, but tell myself there's nothing wrong with fighting Sent to Earth, I don't see the change among the species That's so vibrant with the veins of Mother Nature Views long since changed from that of common legislature Creepin' in prescriptions, I'm showin' symptoms of withdrawal But this placeron smile tells you there's nothing wrong Still I make a beat with my index and middle To represent the peace when I speak and start to spittle With no doubt in your thoughts you would've thought he brought a chisel But that's the magic of a pizzle, misery my company bunkered me Till your thoughts crack like Humpty Dumpty, he is me Guess I'll lean since at the brink of going extinct So rest in peace Pourin' out this drink for Peter Seems like we pourin' out liters",
  "lyricsSegments": [
    {
      "end": 1.3799999952316284,
      "text": "808 caught the jam",
      "start": 0
    },
    {
      "end": 9.15999984741211,
      "text": "DJ Flair, make the money flare",
      "start": 6.940000057220459
    },
    {
      "end": 11.899999618530273,
      "text": "Everywhere I go, I keep a pocket full of dough",
      "start": 9.640000343322754
    },
    {
      "end": 14.34000015258789,
      "text": "Everywhere I go, I keep a wallet full of dough",
      "start": 12.15999984741211
    },
    {
      "end": 16.239999771118164,
      "text": "Nah, fuck that, let's be honest",
      "start": 14.34000015258789
    },
    {
      "end": 18.959999084472656,
      "text": "Every single month, I be waitin' on my food stamps",
      "start": 16.31999969482422
    },
    {
      "end": 21.739999771118164,
      "text": "And if I wasn't rappin', I'd be homeless, thinkin', damn",
      "start": 19.18000030517578
    },
    {
      "end": 24.440000534057617,
      "text": "I am not a grown man, even though I'm grown, man",
      "start": 21.760000228881836
    },
    {
      "end": 27.18000030517578,
      "text": "Keep a foil in my hand, block as hot as oil in the pan",
      "start": 24.440000534057617
    },
    {
      "end": 30.040000915527344,
      "text": "Poppin' bowls till they boil and they burn, boys, take it",
      "start": 27.18000030517578
    },
    {
      "end": 32.540000915527344,
      "text": "Boy, I stay sellin' work, so I smoke for free",
      "start": 30.059999465942383
    },
    {
      "end": 34.79999923706055,
      "text": "I mean, hopefully, I make my re-up",
      "start": 32.540000915527344
    },
    {
      "end": 37.880001068115234,
      "text": "Big bro in blue dreads, bangin' C's up Amoebra",
      "start": 34.97999954223633
    },
    {
      "end": 41.5,
      "text": "I've been spittin' myself so many ways that I feel like Amoeba",
      "start": 38.040000915527344
    },
    {
      "end": 44.97999954223633,
      "text": "Stretchin' myself way too thin, and these drugs don't help",
      "start": 41.84000015258789
    },
    {
      "end": 48.65999984741211,
      "text": "Bein' a thug don't help, I created my own hell, I refuse to ask for help",
      "start": 44.97999954223633
    },
    {
      "end": 51.91999816894531,
      "text": "Since 1993, I've been tryin' to set my mind free",
      "start": 49.119998931884766
    },
    {
      "end": 53.91999816894531,
      "text": "Mind died down by these high beams",
      "start": 51.91999816894531
    },
    {
      "end": 57.119998931884766,
      "text": "As life strikes me like lightning, I keep fightin'",
      "start": 53.91999816894531
    },
    {
      "end": 59.959999084472656,
      "text": "The only feasible outcome, outgunned and eye-strung",
      "start": 57.119998931884766
    },
    {
      "end": 63.439998626708984,
      "text": "I run into the same nightmares that I've had since I was young",
      "start": 60.040000915527344
    },
    {
      "end": 66.37999725341797,
      "text": "So I run, run, run, run away real fast",
      "start": 63.599998474121094
    },
    {
      "end": 69.04000091552734,
      "text": "Take a blast of the glass, knock me back on my ass",
      "start": 66.37999725341797
    },
    {
      "end": 71.94000244140625,
      "text": "So I run, run, run, run away real fast",
      "start": 69.12000274658203
    },
    {
      "end": 74.81999969482422,
      "text": "Take a blast of the glass, knock me back on my ass",
      "start": 71.94000244140625
    },
    {
      "end": 76.23999786376953,
      "text": "There's no more rebels in the fridge",
      "start": 74.81999969482422
    },
    {
      "end": 78.63999938964844,
      "text": "Business getting thin when the pixie burstin' in",
      "start": 76.36000061035156
    },
    {
      "end": 81.62000274658203,
      "text": "And now the business is extinct and I ain't seen it straight in weeks",
      "start": 78.63999938964844
    },
    {
      "end": 84.5999984741211,
      "text": "Exist among the weak, but tell myself there's nothing wrong with fighting",
      "start": 81.62000274658203
    },
    {
      "end": 88.13999938964844,
      "text": "Exist among the weak, but tell myself there's nothing wrong with fighting",
      "start": 85.4800033569336
    },
    {
      "end": 90.41999816894531,
      "text": "Sent to Earth, I don't see the change among the species",
      "start": 88.13999938964844
    },
    {
      "end": 92.37999725341797,
      "text": "That's so vibrant with the veins of Mother Nature",
      "start": 90.41999816894531
    },
    {
      "end": 94.80000305175781,
      "text": "Views long since changed from that of common legislature",
      "start": 92.37999725341797
    },
    {
      "end": 97.68000030517578,
      "text": "Creepin' in prescriptions, I'm showin' symptoms of withdrawal",
      "start": 94.80000305175781
    },
    {
      "end": 101.05999755859375,
      "text": "But this placeron smile tells you there's nothing wrong",
      "start": 97.68000030517578
    },
    {
      "end": 109.95999908447266,
      "text": "Still I make a beat with my index and middle",
      "start": 107.13999938964844
    },
    {
      "end": 112.37999725341797,
      "text": "To represent the peace when I speak and start to spittle",
      "start": 109.95999908447266
    },
    {
      "end": 114.77999877929688,
      "text": "With no doubt in your thoughts you would've thought he brought a chisel",
      "start": 112.41999816894531
    },
    {
      "end": 118,
      "text": "But that's the magic of a pizzle, misery my company bunkered me",
      "start": 114.77999877929688
    },
    {
      "end": 120.27999877929688,
      "text": "Till your thoughts crack like Humpty Dumpty, he is me",
      "start": 118
    },
    {
      "end": 122.08000183105469,
      "text": "Guess I'll lean since at the brink of going extinct",
      "start": 120.27999877929688
    },
    {
      "end": 122.77999877929688,
      "text": "So rest in peace",
      "start": 122.08000183105469
    },
    {
      "end": 124.5199966430664,
      "text": "Pourin' out this drink for Peter",
      "start": 123.04000091552734
    },
    {
      "end": 126.5,
      "text": "Seems like we pourin' out liters",
      "start": 124.72000122070312
    }
  ],
